        faq_title: "Frequently Asked Questions - FAQ",
        faq_q1: "Can I resume daily activities immediately after the procedure?",
        faq_a1: "Yes, you can. Hani's hair stroke technique minimizes skin damage, so your eyebrows won't look overly dark immediately after the procedure. You can attend appointments or go to work on the same day as it looks natural enough.",
        faq_q2: "How long does it last?",
        faq_a2: "Generally, it lasts for 1~3 years. The duration may vary depending on skin type, lifestyle, and sun exposure, and oily skin may fade relatively quickly. We recommend a touch-up after 2 months to enhance the quality, and then annual maintenance procedures to maintain the best results.",
        faq_q3: "Can I choose the color and shape?",
        faq_a3: "We create a design that best suits your bone structure and face shape. About 20~30 minutes before the procedure, precise measurements and design work are conducted, creating a shape that suits your face, not trends. The procedure only proceeds after you confirm and approve the design. Colors are also applied in the most harmonious shade that matches your natural hair color and skin tone.",
        faq_q4: "Does it hurt a lot?",
        faq_a4: "Most customers say they felt almost no pain. We proceed with professional techniques so you can be comfortable throughout the procedure. The sensation is often described as light scratching or tingling, and some clients even fall asleep during the procedure, showing how comfortable the process is. Any discomfort is very mild and temporary.",
        faq_q5: "What is the recovery process?",
        faq_a5: "â€¢ Days 1~2: May appear darker than expected and slightly red (normal reaction!)<br>â€¢ Days 3~5: Thin scabs may form and it may itch â†’ Never scratch or pick them!<br>â€¢ Days 6~10: Scabs fall off naturally and color lightens<br>â€¢ Days 11~28: Original color settles in and becomes very natural<br>â€¢ 2 months after procedure: Recommended touch-up time, quality UP!",
        faq_q6: "Is it safe? Is there a risk of infection?",
        faq_a6: "It is completely safe when performed by a professional. We strictly adhere to the following standards.<br>â€¢ 100% sterilized, disposable needles (opened in front of you)<br>â€¢ Use of premium pigments approved by Korean FDA and European safety standards<br>â€¢ Hospital-grade hygiene and disinfection management<br>â€¢ Use of disposable gloves and consumables<br>If you follow proper aftercare, the risk of infection is virtually 'zero'.",
        faq_q7: "I have existing semi-permanent residue. Can I still get the procedure?",
        faq_a7: "It depends on the concentration and color of the remaining semi-permanent makeup. You need to send unedited eyebrow photos before booking for accurate guidance. If the existing tattoo is too dark, we may recommend laser removal first. However, if the residue color is light, hair stroke technique can often naturally cover it.",
        faq_q8: "Can I wash my face or exercise after the procedure?",
        faq_a8: "On the day of the procedure, please avoid getting water on the treated area. From the next day, light contact with water is okay. To allow the pigment to settle stably, please avoid intense exercise, sauna, and swimming for about a week.",
        faq_q9: "Why should I get lip semi-permanent makeup?",
        faq_a9: "Lip semi-permanent makeup creates clear and defined lips without makeup. Main benefits include:<br>â€¢ Lips with color when you wake up in the morning or right after eating<br>â€¢ Improvement of dull or uneven lip color<br>â€¢ Making thin lips appear fuller and more vibrant<br>â€¢ Natural lip line definition for clear contours<br>â€¢ Waterproof effect that doesn't come off with water or sweat (maintains even during swimming, gym, exercise!)<br>â€¢ Saves daily makeup time",
        faq_q10: "What colors are available?",
        faq_a10: "We have a wide range from natural nude pink to deeper rose and berry tones. Through consultation, we select the optimal color together based on:<br>â€¢ Harmony with skin tone<br>â€¢ Natural matching with original lip color<br>â€¢ Preferred style (natural/bold)<br>â€¢ Color that looks good even without makeup",
        faq_q11: "Does lip semi-permanent hurt more than eyebrows?",
        faq_a11: "Since lips are more sensitive than eyebrows, you may feel a bit more sensation. However, we use professional comfort care techniques designed for lip procedures. Most customers say \"it was better than I thought\" and that it's bearable. You can take breaks during the procedure if needed. It's a brief discomfort, but you'll experience much more beautiful results!",
        faq_q12: "How long does lip semi-permanent last?",
        faq_a12: "Generally, it lasts for 2~5 years. Since lip skin structure is different, it tends to last longer than eyebrows. Factors affecting duration include:<br>â€¢ Smoking can accelerate color fading<br>â€¢ Sun exposure affects color<br>â€¢ Using exfoliating lip products can cause faster fading<br>â€¢ Individual metabolic rate<br>You can complete the most beautiful color and longevity through a touch-up about 2 months after the procedure.",
        faq_q13: "What is the recovery process for lip semi-permanent?",
        faq_a13: "â€¢ Days 1~3: May be swollen, appear darker, and slightly sensitive â†’ Ice compress recommended!<br>â€¢ Days 4~7: Skin may peel, feel dry and tight â†’ Moisturize thoroughly!<br>â€¢ Days 8~14: Color may fade significantly and appear patchy<br>â€¢ Weeks 3~4: Original color settles and develops naturally<br>â€¢ After 2 months: Time for touch-up to complete the color<br><br>Important Aftercare<br>â€¢ Apply healing ointment/moisturizer 6~8 times a day for the first week<br>â€¢ Avoid hot, spicy, and oily foods for 1 week<br>â€¢ No kissing for 10 days<br>â€¢ Use a straw for drinks<br>â€¢ No swimming or sauna for 2 weeks<br>We'll explain more detailed aftercare methods after the procedure!",
        faq_q14: "Can I still wear lipstick after lip semi-permanent?",
        faq_a14: "Of course! After recovery is complete, you can freely apply any lipstick you want. Since lip semi-permanent serves as a base color, many customers are satisfied without lipstick in daily life and only use it on special occasions. Also, since the lip line is defined, it reduces lipstick bleeding.",
        faq_q15: "Who should not get the procedure?",
        faq_a15: "We do not proceed with appointments for the following cases:<br>â€¢ Pregnant or breastfeeding<br>â€¢ Active herpes/cold sores on lips (consultation required to determine possibility)<br>â€¢ Undergoing cancer treatment<br>â€¢ Bleeding disorders<br>â€¢ Taking blood thinners<br>â€¢ Skin conditions on the treatment area<br>â€¢ Keloid-prone individuals<br>If you have medical conditions, we recommend consulting with a doctor before the procedure.",
        
